Kenya Power and Lighting Company have announced Industrial Attachment opportunities for continuing Bachelor’s Degree, Diploma and Craft Certificate students. “In line with the Government’s commitment to supporting youth empowerment, we are offering to continue Bachelor’s Degree, Diploma and Craft Certificate students an exciting opportunity to gain hands-on work experience and develop key employability skills.” KPLC tweeted. According to a statement by KPLC, the attachment will take a three month period from May to July 2022. The interested candidates should be available full time for three months. Applicants should be continuing students from recognized institutions and have valid introduction letters from their schools. “Students pursuing Craft Certificate in Electrical and Electronics Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering are also encouraged to apply,” the notice stated. Further, the company has encouraged Persons living with Disabilities to apply. KPLC has advised all interested students to submit their applications online at the Kenya Powe website: http://www.kplc.co.ke under the Public information tab and Career Opportunities section. “Applications should be received no later than 30th March 2022,” KPLC insisted.